text: Captain Moussa Dadis Camara (born 1 January 1964)http://eur- lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:L:2009:281:0007:0011:EN:PDF now called Moïse Dadis Camara is an ex-officer of the Guinean army. He was the President of the Republic of Guinea's National Council for Democracy and Development (Conseil National de la Démocratie et du Développement, CNDD) from 2008 until 2010. On March 28, 2025, he was pardoned by the transitional president, Mamady Doumbouya. ==References== Category:1964 births Category:Presidents of Guinea Category:Living people
